name: Long-distance running
description: In modern human society, long-distance running has multiple purposes for physical body  strength.

name: Squats & Knee Position
description: Everyone has heard the phrase repeatedly, over the past 5 years or so, while squatting, “drive your knees out.” This can be a great cue when used appropriately, however, it has almost become obnoxious with everyone and their mothers yelling this phrase.

name: Hammer Curls
description: Hammer curls are similar to biceps curls but are performed with the palms facing each other throughout the movement.

name: Weightlifting
description: Weightlifting generally refers to activities in which people lift weights, often in the form of dumbbells or barbells. People lift various kinds of weights for a variety of different reasons. These may include competition to determine which competitor can lift the most weight; promoting health and fitness; developing physical strength; or developing a muscular physique,

name: The cable machine
description: The cable machine is a large piece of gym equipment that has adjustable cable pulleys. The resistance of the cables allows you to perform numerous exercises in a variety of directions. Some machines have one or two cable stations, while others have multiple.

name: Kettlebell Exercises
description: Most kettlebell workouts include squats, lunges, crunches, and other moves that work your abs and other core muscles. Arms: Yes. The kettlebell is used as a weight for arm exercises like single-arm rows and shoulder presses.
